Amir Khan says Floyd Mayweather 'is scared'
Media playback is not supported on this deviceBritain's Amir Khan says Floyd Mayweather "is scared" of fighting him after the Americanopted to face Andre Berto on 12 September.Khan had hoped for a September bout with Mayweather, 38, afterbeating Chris Algieri in June.Khan thought he was close to securing a meeting with the sport's pound-for-pound king after his success over American fighter Algieri and Mayweather'sunanimous points victory over Manny Pacquiaoin their lucrative meeting in May.